Little did we know that Americans would be dividing themselves into Betophobes and Betophiles.
Beto O’Rourke is running on a platform that’s vague, and, for both Betophiles and Betophobes, it’s the lack of ideology that attracts or repels them.
Anyone who remembers 2008 will recognize the echoes of Barack Obama, who offered “unity over division” and similar promises.
But the elections of Barack Obama and Donald Trump—along with a strong showing by Bernie Sanders in 2016—changed people’s sense of what’s possible and what’s advantageous.
That is to say, he appeals to those who love Barack Obama, hate Donald Trump, and pay scant attention to news about politics.